result.execSummary:
The defendant Gary S Williams Sr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Gary S Williams in court with attorney George Andrew Limbeck.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:03 PM. Called 15CF70, 16CF29 and 16CF52. State - here for sentencing after receiving PSI. State and counsel are prepared to proceed and both have received a copy of the PSI. State - no amendments, changes or modifications needed as far as he is concerned. Limbeck - does not believe anything dramtically affects his client refers to page 14 in regards to someone being deceased, clarifies the record. Court so notes but does not think it makes any difference in regards to the PSI. No testimomy today, just argument by counsel. State makes a remark in regards to it looks like the only order for PSI was on 15CF70 and that is the only case that a PSI was done on. Limbeck notices that as well now that the State has brought it to his attention. Both parties will be referencing the minutes from the 7/25/17 in regards to sentence recommendations. After further discussion, parties remember that the PSI was only supposed to be done on 15CF70 and they had an agreement on the other two cases, 16CF29 and 16CF52. Court agrees and will proceed today. State makes final argument prior to sentencing recommendation - on 16CF29 - 180 days jail - ordered first with prison term to run consecutive to this case - State asking for consecutive time but defense is free to argue for concurrent time; 16CF52 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years - consecutive to 15CF70 - with defense free to argue on concurrent or consecutive. Limbeck agrees. State - sentencing on counts #1 and #6 on 15CF70 - State recommends 7 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES; on count #3 - 3 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 1 year of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES; on 16CF52 - asking for the probation to run consecutive to the ES for stated reasons - continues making argument for his recommendations. Court has question on State's recommendations in regards to 15CF70, clarifies that the prison time requested on that case is concurrent or consecutive to each other. State - concurrent to each other. Limbeck makes final argument prior to his recommendations - recommends conditional jail time and time to report to allow him to serve his sentence in the Shawano County Jail. Williams makes statement, has people in Court today that would like to speak on his behalf. Recess to allow parties to decide if someone will speak on the defendant's behalf. Back on record at 1:46 PM. Court allows Judy Murphy to make statement to the Court on behalf of the defendant. Murphy makes statement. Williams makes an additonal comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 15CF70 - counts #1 and #6 - 7 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - concurrent to each other, count #3 - 3 years consisting of 1 year of initial confinement plus 2 years of ES - concurrent to counts #1 and #6; 16CF29 - count #1 - 180 days in FC jail - concurrent to 15CF70, 16CF52 - place on probation for 2 years - concurrent to ES on 15CF70; court costs on all counts on all cases, submit DNA sample on all counts on each case, no possession of firearms, no voting, right to appeal, not eligible CIP but is eligible for SAP, right to appeal, set aside bond forfeiture in 16CF29 and use any bonds posted to pay costs/remainder due in 60 days/CJ, credit can be determined by counsel, adjourned.

Defendant Gary S Williams in court with attorney George Andrew Limbeck.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:03 AM. Called 15CF70, 16CF52 and 16CF29. State - resolved - defense counsel will be requesting a PSI and State has no objection to the PSI being requested. Limbeck agrees. Limbeck puts agreement on the record - 15CF70 - plead G to counts #1, #3 and #6 as alleged, remaining counts to be DRI; 16CF29 - plead NC to count #1 and remaining count to be DRI; 16CF52 - plead NC to counts #1 and amend count #2 to misd BJ charge and then a NC plea would be entered to the amended count and dismiss and read in remaining counts; on 15CF70 - request for a PSI with both parties free to argue, 16CF29 - joint recommendation of 180 days in FC jail - free to argue for concurrent or consecutive to sentnece ordered on 15CF70; 16CF52 - State recommends a withheld sentence and place on probation for 2 years - consecutive to sentence on 15CF70 but defense is free to argue for consecutive or concurrent. State and Williams agree. State moves to amend count #2 to misd bail jumping contrary to 946.49(1)(a). Court amends count #2 to misd bail jumping after hearing no objections to that amendment. Defendant understands what it means for a count to be DRI. Thru the plea questionnaire, defendant pleads G to counts #1, #3 and #6 as alleged; pleads NC to count #1 on 16CF29 and pleads NC to count #1 as alleged on 16CF52 and count #2 as amended on the record. Court dismisses and reads in counts #2, #4, #5, #7, #8 and #9 on 15CF70, dismisses and reads in count #2 on 16CF29 and dismisses and reads in counts #3 and #4 on 16CF52. Court goes thru plea questionnaire, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived is constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, continues bond on all cases and orders a PSI. Court sets all cases for sentencing hearing. Defense puts new address on the record.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 7, 2017 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Gary S Williams in court with attorney William Allen Dickens.  Defendant Gary S Williams in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:48 PM. Called 15CF70, 16CF29 and 16CF52. Dickens informs Court that he is appearing specially today. State - scheduled for PH on 16CF52, AIA on 16CF29 and FPT on 15CF70. State has submitted to the Court exhibits #1 - copy of bond on 15CF70, #2 - copy of bond on 16CF29 and #3 - copy of bond on 16CF13. Court receives after no objections. Dickens - going forth with PH on 16CF52. State calls Lt. Jeff Marvin. Marvin sworn in at 1:50 PM. Direct exam by State. Record reflects proper identification of the defendant (1:52 PM). Marvin excused at 1:56 PM. Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed, binds over for trial. State files Information that mirrors the complaint. Dickens has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas. Court accepts plea, continues bond, sets 16CF52 for FPT on 9/15/16 at 10:45 AM. Court address 16CF29. Dickens has complaint, waives reading of it, will be waiving PH on that matter. Court goes thru verbal waiver of PH collaquey. Dickens and Williams understand and are willing to waive PH. Court finds probable cause, binds over for trial, set for ARGN. Dickens willing to proceed to ARGN as State will file Information that will mirror the complaint, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, sets this matter for FPT on 9/15/16 at 10:45 AM. State - bond on 16CF29 - asks for $600.00 cash (original $500.00 has been ordered forfeited). Dickens makes argument for lower bond or signature bond due to health conditions of the defendant. Court - bond - sets bond at an addtional $500.00 cash bond at this point with same conditions. State - 15CF70 - would prefer to set the matter for trial if it is not resolved. Court will set 15CF70 for JT on 9/15/16 at 8:30 AM.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 15, 2016 at 10:45 am.
Adjourned initial appearance on June 21, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
